We believe that analysis of your company and your customers is key in responding effectively to your promotional needs and we will work with you to fully understand your business. We seek the miracle. We seek the parting of the seas, the moving of the mountains. But no, it's a quiet thing. At least for me it was.[/vc_column_text][tlg_spacer height="30"][vc_column_text][tlg_dropcap text="B" background="#f05660" color="#fff"]eing in L.A. has definitely given me the opportunity to experience how my music sounds in real life because I can drive around and listen to the mixes, which I couldn't do in New York. We believe that analysis of your company and your customers is key in responding effectively to your promotional needs and we will work with you to fully understand your business. I get to feel how a song works in combination with a sunset and a drive through the mountains.[/vc_column_text][tlg_spacer height="30"][vc_column_text][tlg_dropcap text="A" background="#f00" color="#fff"]t present, I am mainly observing the physical motion of mountains, water, trees and flowers. We believe that analysis of your company and your customers is key in responding effectively to your promotional needs and we will work with you to fully understand your business. One is everywhere reminded of similar movements in the human body, of similar impulses of joy and suffering in plants.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][/vc_column][/vc_row]

As 2015 comes to an end, were looking back at some of our favorite Weekend Hashtag Projects of the year. We featured Mike Gutkins (@mc_gutty) photo for #WHP????, our first emoji hashtag project that followed the landmark United States Supreme Court decision to legalize marriage for all. Mike took this shot while walking in the New York City Gay Pride Parade, a scene he describes as electric and full of joy. As I marched down Fifth Avenue, my eyes were drawn to every single person around me. Rainbow colors streaking across the participants and their floats were equal to the sea of rainbow colors in the onlooking crowds, says Mike. It was a triumphant and prideful moment in the heart of New York City with one of the most iconic buildings as the background. Stay tuned for more #WHPlookbacks as we count down to 2016! Photo for #WHP???? by @mc_gutty

item.title: Privacy Policy
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Transparency and Choice

This privacy policy discloses the privacy practices for our shop. It will notify you of the following:
  • What personally identifiable information is collected from you through the web site, how it is used and with whom it may be shared.
  • What choices are available to you regarding the use of your data.
  • How you can correct any inaccuracies in the information.

Information Collection, Use, and Sharing

We respect your privacy and do not spam and will never sell, rent, lease or give away your information to any third party. We only have access to/collect information that you voluntarily give us via email or other direct contact from you. We will use your information to respond to you, regarding the reason you contacted us. We will not share your information with any third party outside of our organization, other than as necessary to fulfill your request.

Personal Information

You may opt out of any future contacts from us at any time. You can do the following at any time by changing the profile information in our site:
  • See what data we have about you, if any.
  • Change/correct any data we have about you.
  • Have us delete any data we have about you.
  • Express any concern you have about our use of your data.

Security

We take precautions to protect your information. When you submit sensitive information via the website, your information is protected both online and offline. Unless you ask us not to, we may contact you via email in the future to tell you about specials, new products or services, or changes to this privacy policy.

item.content:encoded: [vc_row full_width="stretch_row"][vc_column][tlg_header_single subtitle_before="yes" a_line="yes" btn_link="url:%23book|||" button_layout="btn btn-filled btn-rounded" icon="" enable_button_2="yes" btn_link_2="url:%23|||" button_layout_2="btn btn-rounded" icon_2="ti-control-play" customize_font="yes" title_font="0" subtitle_font="La Belle Aurore:tlg://fonts.gstatic.com/s/labelleaurore/v7/Irdbc4ASuUoWDjd_Wc3md123K2iuuhwZgaKapkyRTY8.ttf:tlg:regular" content_font="0" title="Perfect Haircut for Your Hair" subtitle="The Hottest Hairstyles" image="4730" button_text="Book an appointment" button_text_2="Play video" modal_embed_2="https://vimeo.com/176283349" title_size="79" subtitle_size="40"][/tlg_header_single][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" tlg_background_style="bg-secondary" css=".vc_custom_1476177837285{background-color: #eaeaea !important;}"][vc_column][tlg_intro_content layout="halfscreen-right" icon="" image="4729" title="Welcome To Wanium Barber"]Basically a barbershop is a place where people go to cut their hair and of course it is the working place of a barber. A barber is a person whose livelihood is mainly to cut, dress, groom, style and shave mens and boys hair and in some cases ladies / girls who keep low cut.[/tlg_intro_content][tlg_intro_content layout="halfscreen-left" icon="" css_animation="bottom-to-top" image="4747" title="Who We Are"]A barber's place of work is known as a barber shop or a barber's. Barber shops are also places of social interaction and public discourse. In some instances, barbershops are also public forums. They are the locations of open debates, voicing public concerns, and engaging citizens in discussions about contemporary issues. They were also influential in helping shape male identity.[/tlg_intro_content][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][tlg_headings separator="line_icon" icon="ti-cut" css_animation="bottom-to-top" title="Our Services" subtitle="Multiple services in our shop" icon_color="#bf9457"][tlg_intro_carousel style="box-top" css_animation="bottom-to-top"][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4739" title="Haircut $35"] The fashioning of hair can be considered an aspect of personal grooming.[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4742" title="Sides Cut $40"]The popular considerations also influence some hairstyles.[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4738" title="Clipper Cut $15"]Hairstyles are markers and signifiers of social class, age, marital status.[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4737" title="Head Shave $45"]Racial identification, political beliefs, and attitudes about gender.[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4740" title="Face Shave $30"]Arguably the precursor of most plain modern male styles[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][tlg_intro_carousel_content layout="boxed" icon="" image="4741" title="Beard Trim $30"]Men wore their hair short, and either parted on the side or in the middle.[/tlg_intro_carousel_content][/tlg_intro_carousel][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row tlg_background_style="bg-dark" tlg_text_align="text-center"
